<br />
  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">ADVENTURE DECK STRATEGY<br />
<br />
The sites in this deck are not important except for the Lothlorien Woods and Slopes of Amon Hen.  The woods allows you to spot your site six, giving Uruviel a huge Strength bonus.  Also, the Slopes of Amon Hen allow you to come with a serious Uruk-Hai beating, if your opponent gets to site 9.<br />
<br />
FREE PEOPLES STRATEGY<br />
<br />
The idea of this deck is fairly simple.    The small Fellowship really limits Twilight for your opponent, and they will not be able to play many minions at all.  Use Legolas to shoot any incoming minions, and Arwen will do clean up skirmishes.  Once you give Arwen an Elven Bow, most Shadow cards played will not even see a skirmish.  The Allies in this deck are their mostly to aid with Archery, using their special Archery actions.  Give another Elven Bow to Uruviel.  Play Swan-ship to bring your allies to the front lines whenever the situation requires it, usually at site 5, 7, 8, and 9.  Haldir will join the Fellowship at these sites, giving another helping hand in the final steps toward winning the game.<br />
<br />
SHADOW STRATEGY<br />
<br />
The strategy of the Uruk-hai is simple.  Kill Companions.  With Worry, every time an Uruk-Hai wins a skirmish, the Ring-Bearer must exert or take a burden.  The Uruk-Hai Swords and Bred for Battles will help boost your Uruk-Hai to double-digit Strength.  Use Uruk-Hai Rampage to make them Fierce whenever Twilight is available, and you have a single minion doing 4 Vitality of damage every turn.  This should definitely slow the opponent&#39;s Fellowship enough for you to rush ahead and win.<br />
<br />
